                "nameinfo": "Solar <br>System<br> Hiking Trail",
                "divcontentleftinfo_SMXS":"<p>The Solar System Trail project was conceived within the scope of the activities of the <a href='https://astrocamp.astro.up.pt/en/' target='_blank'>AstroCamp</a>, a scientific summer camp that takes place every year at <a href='https://www.paredesdecoura.pt/locais/centro-de-educacao-e-interpretacao-ambiental/' target='_blank'>CEIA – Centre for Environmental Interpretation and Education of the Corno de Bico Protected Landscape</a>. Under the coordination of the astrophysicist <a href='http://astro.up.pt/caup/index.php?WID=114&CID=1&ID=50&Lang=uk' target='_blank'>Carlos Martins</a>, more than 20 Portugues and foreign researchers in astronomy and physics have collaborated in the AstroCamp scientific activities, providing students from eligible countries inspiring and high-quality training, rest and leisure in a secluded and tranquil setting, away from the stress of urban centers.</p>", 
                "divcontentrightinfo_SMXS":"<p>In a second stage <a href='https://www.paredesdecoura.pt/locais/centro-de-educacao-e-interpretacao-ambiental/' target='_blank'>CEIA – Centre for Environmental Interpretation and Education of the Corno de Bico Protected Landscape </a> and the <a href='https://www.paredesdecoura.pt/' target='_blank'>Paredes de Coura Municipality</a> proposed the implementation of a more appealing and functional version of the trail. The <a href='https://astro.up.pt/index.php?Lang=uk' target='_blank'>Center for Astrophysics of the University of Porto</a> through its <a href='http://www.iastro.pt/' target='_blank'>Institute of Astrophysics and Space Sciences</a> and the <a href='http://planetario.up.pt/' target='_blank'>Porto Planetarium – Centro Ciência Viva</a> developed the project, expanding the trail to include text and visual information on the Solar System. At this point the hiking trail was validated by the <a href='http://www.cienciaviva.pt/en/' target='_blank'>Ciência Viva</a> science outreach agency, and it is also being integrated in the Paredes de Coura municipality’s network of walking trails, with the reference number PR17.</p>",
                "divcontentleftinfo_LG":"<p>The Solar System Trail project was conceived within the scope of the activities of the <a href='https://astrocamp.astro.up.pt/en/' target='_blank'>AstroCamp</a>, a scientific summer camp that takes place every year at <a href='https://www.paredesdecoura.pt/locais/centro-de-educacao-e-interpretacao-ambiental/' target='_blank'>CEIA – Centre for Environmental Interpretation and Education of the Corno de Bico Protected Landscape</a>. Under the coordination of the astrophysicist <a href='http://astro.up.pt/caup/index.php?WID=114&CID=1&ID=50&Lang=uk' target='_blank'>Carlos Martins</a>, more than 20 Portugues and foreign researchers in astronomy and physics have collaborated in the AstroCamp scientific activities, providing students from eligible countries inspiring and high-quality training, rest and leisure in a secluded and tranquil setting, away from the stress of urban centers.</p>", 
