                "divcontentleftinfo_MDXL":"<p>The Solar System Trail project was conceived within the scope of the activities of the <a href='https://astrocamp.astro.up.pt/en/' target='_blank'>AstroCamp</a>, a scientific summer camp that takes place every year at <a href='https://www.paredesdecoura.pt/locais/centro-de-educacao-e-interpretacao-ambiental/' target='_blank'>CEIA – Centre for Environmental Interpretation and Education of the Corno de Bico Protected Landscape</a>. Under the coordination of the astrophysicist <a href='http://astro.up.pt/caup/index.php?WID=114&CID=1&ID=50&Lang=uk' target='_blank'>Carlos Martins</a>, more than 20 Portugues and foreign researchers in astronomy and physics have collaborated in the AstroCamp scientific activities, providing students from eligible countries inspiring and high-quality training, rest and leisure in a secluded and tranquil setting, away from the stress of urban centers.</p>", 
